      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions] Line 31: Config normalization does not clamp initialBitrateKbps to the normalized min/max bounds, and targetBitrate_/lastStableBitrate_ are initialized before any validation. A caller providing initialBitrateKbps outside the limits starts the controller outside its configured range until the first decrease/increase path happens to clamp it; update() can return that invalid value unchanged. Normalize limits first, then clamp the initial target.\n```suggestion\n    if (cfg_.minBitrateKbps \u003e cfg_.maxBitrateKbps)\n        std::swap(cfg_.minBitrateKbps, cfg_.maxBitrateKbps);\n\n    targetBitrate_ \u003d clampBitrate(cfg_.initialBitrateKbps);\n    lastStableBitrate_ \u003d targetBitrate_;\n```",
      "revId": "60859830511dd21198f01142169fc71fb5feaeb9",
