      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions] Line 32: Only increaseRampTime and reduction factors are validated. Other configurable floats directly affect state transitions and EWMA math; negative or out-of-range values for lossAlpha/rttAlpha, congestionThreshold, decreaseCooldownSec, or probeDelaySec can create unstable behavior, inverted cooldowns, or EWMA values outside the sample range. Clamp or reject all public Config fields with sane bounds in the constructor.\n```suggestion\n    cfg_.lossAlpha \u003d std::clamp(cfg_.lossAlpha, 0.0f, 1.0f);\n    cfg_.rttAlpha \u003d std::clamp(cfg_.rttAlpha, 0.0f, 1.0f);\n    cfg_.congestionThreshold \u003d std::clamp(cfg_.congestionThreshold, 0.0f, 1.0f);\n    cfg_.decreaseCooldownSec \u003d std::max(cfg_.decreaseCooldownSec, 0.0f);\n    cfg_.probeDelaySec \u003d std::max(cfg_.probeDelaySec, 0.0f);\n    cfg_.minIncreaseFactor \u003d std::max(cfg_.minIncreaseFactor, 0.0f);\n    cfg_.maxIncreaseFactor \u003d std::max(cfg_.maxIncreaseFactor, cfg_.minIncreaseFactor);\n```",
