      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions] Line 725: The controller is seeded from codecVideo-\u003ebitrate only once, but setNewBitrate() never feeds externally-applied/clamped bitrate changes back into bwController_. If sender_-\u003esetBitrate() clamps internally, encoder restart changes constraints, or another path changes videoBitrateInfo_.videoBitrateCurrent, the controller keeps computing from a stale target and can immediately undo the actual encoder bitrate on the next RTCP/audio/REMB event. Keep the controller synchronized whenever a bitrate is accepted. For example:\n```suggestion\n        if (videoBitrateInfo_.videoBitrateCurrent !\u003d newBR) {\n            videoBitrateInfo_.videoBitrateCurrent \u003d newBR;\n            bwController_.setTargetBitrate(newBR);\n            storeVideoBitrateInfo();\n```\nIf setTargetBitrate() resetting lastStableBitrate_ is not desired on controller-originated changes, add a separate syncCurrentBitrate() API that only updates targetBitrate_.",
